<includeonly>{{#if:{{{value|}}}|{{!}}-
! {{#if:{{{label|}}}|{{{label}}}|{{#show:Property:{{{prop|}}}|?Display label|default={{{prop|}}}}}}}
{{!}} {{{value|}}}|}}</includeonly><noinclude>
One property row inside a category display wikitable. Suppressed when
`value` is empty so callers don't need to guard each row.

Label resolution (in order):

# '''`label`''' param — used verbatim when set. Auto-generated
  dispatchers pass this so zero SMW queries fire per row.
# '''`prop`''' param — when `label` is absent, looks up the property's
  `Display label` via `#show`. Use in hand-written custom display
  templates to pick up the site-wide label without hard-coding it.
# '''property name''' — when neither display label is resolvable,
  falls back to the raw property name.

Parameters: `value`, and either `label` (baked) or `prop` (dynamic).
</noinclude>
